# LiveEd API contract

LiveEd builder client code must call a single endpoint:

- `GET|POST /liveed/api.php?action=<action>[&key=value...]`

## Canonical client helper

Use `liveed/modules/api.js#getApiUrl(basePath, action, params)` to build all
LiveEd API URLs.

- `action` is required and is encoded as a query parameter.
- `params` are appended as query parameters.
- POST requests should still send `action` in the URL query string and use the
  request body only for payload fields.

## Supported actions (current)

- `list-blocks` (GET)
- `load-block` (GET, `file`)
- `load-draft` (GET, `id`)
- `save-draft` (POST, `id`, `content`, optional `timestamp`)
- `save-content` (POST, `id`, `content`)
